					<description><![CDATA[<p>Moment Energy Expands With New Series B Raise Moment Energy has raised more than US$40 million in new Series B funding. The round brings total capital raised to over US$100</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/moment-energy-raises-us40m-to-scale-second-life-battery-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal">Moment Energy Raises US$40M To Scale Second-Life Battery Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Moment Energy Expands With New Series B Raise</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Moment Energy has raised more than US$40 million in new Series B funding. The round brings total capital raised to over US$100 million. It was led by Evok Innovations with support from Liberty Mutual Investments, W23 Global Fund and Acario. Existing backers also took part.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company builds commercial energy storage systems using repurposed EV batteries. Demand is growing across data centres, utilities and industrial sites. The new capital will expand manufacturing across the US and Canada. It will scale engineering teams and increase production output.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The energy sector is under pressure from rising AI demand. Data centres require stable power. Many grids are aging and cannot keep pace. Battery supply chains are also strained. Repurposed EV batteries offer a domestic solution. Moment Energy is positioned to meet this need.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The firm says its goal is simple. It wants to improve grid resilience and reduce energy costs. Its systems deploy quickly and use batteries already on the road. This supports national energy security and cuts infrastructure delays.</span></p>
<h2><b>Second-Life Batteries Move Into Commercial Deployment</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Moment Energy has moved second-life storage from trials to commercial scale. It is the first company in North America with certified systems built from repurposed EV batteries. It holds UL 1974 and UL 9540A safety certifications. This removes deployment barriers for commercial sites.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its proprietary pack-swapping design extends system life. Most storage systems last around fifteen years. Moment Energy extends this to thirty years. Its economics also shift the cost curve. Cycling costs fall to as low as three cents per kWh. Industrial customers benefit from lower long-term energy spend.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company also builds systems with one of the highest energy densities in the market. Its platform delivers up to 164 MWh per acre. This supports dense sites like data centres. It also improves land value for industrial operators.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Moment Energy calls its approach a real example of Physical AI. It uses deep data on battery health and chemistry. This enables safe and predictable performance at scale. Investors say this capability sets the firm apart in a complex sector.</span></p>
<h2><b>Growing Demand From AI And Industrial Infrastructure</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_200644" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200644" class="size-full wp-image-200644" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Moment-2.png" alt="AI data centres increasing energy demand, supported by second-life battery storage systems stabilising industrial grids and infrastructure." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-200644" class="wp-caption-text">Rising AI infrastructure demand is reshaping global energy systems, with second-life battery technologies enabling faster deployment, grid stability, and reliable power for industrial and commercial applications. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">AI is changing energy demand patterns. Data centres now require far more power. Many regions cannot supply enough capacity. This has created new pressure on planning systems. It has also raised costs for large operators.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Moment Energy addresses these issues. Its repurposed batteries support rapid deployment. They also offer domestic supply resilience. This reduces delays from global manufacturing issues. It also supports markets that need local production.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Utilities are exploring second-life storage for grid support. Industrial facilities are seeking stable backup power. Hospitals, factories and microgrids are also adopting the technology. Growth is driven by reliability needs and lower total costs.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company believes second-life systems will define the next energy wave. The market is shifting from early trials to large deployments. Commercial customers now want long-term, certifiable solutions. Moment Energy has entered this space ahead of competitors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/andreessen-horowitz-raises-2-2b-crypto-fund-to-back-blockchain-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Andreessen Horowitz Raises $2.2B Crypto Fund To Back Blockchain Infrastructure</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Strategic Positioning And Future Market Outlook</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series B round strengthens the firm’s leadership in North America. It plans to expand across key US regions. These include high-growth areas with strong data centre demand. Canada will also remain a core base for new facilities.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its manufacturing strategy focuses on domestic resilience. This approach aligns with new policy incentives. It supports shorter supply chains and more predictable production. It also reduces the environmental impact of early battery recycling.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Demand for repurposed storage continues to rise. Battery availability is growing as more EVs reach replacement cycles. These packs still hold significant value. Moment Energy uses its platform to capture that value.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The firm says each battery deserves a second life. Its systems prevent early disposal. They also support a more circular energy economy. This appeals to both industrial buyers and climate-driven investors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is now seen as a key supplier for next-generation infrastructure. Its safety record and certifications strengthen this position. Its technology also lowers costs for long-term operations. These advantages shape its future </span><a href="https://www.awork.com/glossary/roadmap" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">roadmap</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/moment-energy-raises-us40m-to-scale-second-life-battery-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal">Moment Energy Raises US$40M To Scale Second-Life Battery Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
